docs.lead_paragraph: SEABRIGHT, N.J., Aug. 23. -- The West End Express on the New Jersey Southern Railroad, due here at 6 o'clock, ran into a carriage containing a driving party at the North Borough crossing this evening. Three of the occupants were instantly killed, and the other three more or less badly injured. The dead are:

headline.main: THREE KILLED BY A TRAIN; Son and Sisters-in-Law of Charles W. Trippe Dead at Seabright. NO WARNING AT THE CROSSING Mrs. Trippe, Her Baby, and Nurse, Who Were Also in the Carriage, More or Less Injured.
